d distance between the cluster centers is 1.3 Mpc and\nthe los velocity difference is 1750 km/s. A dynamical analysis of the system\nshows that the two clusters are likely to be gravitationally bound, in a\npre-merger phase, with CIZAJ1824 in front of RXCJ1825 and going toward it. Our\nresults corroborate a picture where the Lyra region is the place of a very\ncomplex scenario of cluster assembly.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 6 Aug 2019 17:58:32 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 21 Oct 2019 10:37:27 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-01-22"}
