ears, perhaps suggesting that episodic\nwarming mechanisms were not needed. Atmospheric collapse and permanently\nglaciated conditions occur once surface ice coverage exceeds a threshold\ndepending on CIA assumptions. Our results support an early warm and semi-arid\nclimate consistent with many geologic observations.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 7 Aug 2019 14:09:21 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sun, 11 Aug 2019 08:12:27 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Wed, 11 Mar 2020 09:30:29 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-03-12"}
