ty of\nthis alternative scenario has been assessed within the kinematic context of the\nstellar neighbourhood of the Sun, using data from Gaia second data release, and\ntwo robust solar sibling candidates have been identified. Our results suggest\nthat comets coming from interstellar space at low heliocentric velocities may\nnot be rare.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 7 Aug 2019 14:54:24 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 27 Aug 2019 17:54:58 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Wed, 28 Aug 2019 20:25:52 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-08-30"}
